 Simone Buchner with her dancers, front from left, Hannah Ferreira, Cayla Truter and Channae Erens
Port Elizabeth’s Ellen Bunting Dance Academy is producing a new show Elements of Dance at the PE Opera House on Friday and Saturday, November 3 and 4.
Academy principal Simone Buchner has put together a nostalgic and entertaining journey which celebrates the various “elements” of dance such as ballet, tap, modern, jazz and hip-hop.
She hopes the audience will get their feet tapping as the show moves across time and music with this on-stage theatrical dance production featuring well-known hits and colourful costumes.
Director and producer Buchner has incorporated a wide range of disciplines in Elements of Dance. ranging from modern and tap all the way through to lyrical and broadway jazz.
It will feature a kaleidoscope of numbers from tap-dancing children to Broadway jazz and even a Greek-inspired twist to a tap number.
Elements of Dance will be at the Opera House on Friday at 7.30pm and next Saturday at 2.30pm and 7.30pm. Tickets at R120 are on sale at Computicket.

